Usage<11;1>
-----<13;5>
ae [filename]<15;1>
Read or create a text file; default filename is `a.txt`.  Text files consists of<16;2>
lines of printable text, tabs, or newline characters.  A physical line can be o<17;1>
f arbitrary length and is delimited by either a newline or the end of file.  Tab<18;2>
stops are every eight columns.  The behaviour of non-printable characters may v<19;1>
ary depending on the implementation of the Curses library, `stty(1)` settings, o<20;1>
r terminal emulator.<23;1>
